
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-bhatia-bgp-multiple-next-hops-01.txt'>
    <title>"Advertising Multiple NextHop Routes in BGP", Manav Bhatia</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-bhatia-bgp-multiple-next-hops-01.txt</link>
    <description>This document describes an extensible mechanism that allows a BGP speaker to advertise multiple BGP paths for a destination to its peers, by describing a new BGP capability, termed "Multiple-Hop Capability". The mechanisms described in this document are applicable to all routers, both those with the ability to inject multiple routing entries in their forwarding table and those without.</description>
    <dc:date>2006-08-09T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
